Solutions Architecture Advisor
quebec
Montreal, Quebec, Canada
Please note that this position is located in Levis. Candidates must have an eligible work permit for Canada and be fluent in French.
Do you want to experience the essence of a large organization in a company with a personal touch? Come and work with us! We are looking for creative, innovative, and collaborative people like you to join our team.
At the heart of Alithya’s values is the well-being of our employees and their families. That's why we continue to follow the Public Health Agency of Canada’s recommendations closely.
We remain close to you, while keeping our distance via Phone, Skype, Zoom or however you like.
Take your ambitions to the next level
We are looking for a BI Solutions Architecture Advisor whose mandates will be divided between different initiatives.
He/she will be responsible for designing the BI solution architecture to meet the business needs of the various damage insurance business sectors. He/she will also support the delivery teams during the implementation of the solutions.
The Architecture Advisor will work closely with business stakeholders, managers, and members of his/her team and projects.
Within the framework of various initiatives, accompany and guide users in the analysis and definition of needs;
Coordinate studies, as well as positioning, feasibility and detailed design phases and make appropriate recommendations;
Advise and support your partners in the positioning, planning, development, implementation and follow-up of various projects;
Design BI application architecture by selecting appropriate technologies for integration, transformation and automated deployment;
Develop, implement and enforce conceptual and logical models, design, implementation and integration strategies;
Ensure cross-functional coordination with the authorities involved in the projects and provide the required support and follow-ups;
Oversee the implementation projects required to ensure the quality, performance, reliability, availability and continuous improvement of systems and technological solutions;
Identify and describe the functional capabilities required to support the expressed needs;
Apply the norms and standards in force in order to design compliant solutions that respect the company's orientations;
Collaborate closely with project teams and squads in the solution design and implementation process; act as a facilitator in his/her area of responsibility;
Describe solutions in the form of standardized architecture diagrams (Archimate/UML);
Be able to communicate with different audiences (business analysts, functional or organic analysts, developers, solution and software architecture advisors, Scrum Master, delivery manager, manager, etc.).
When it just clicks!
Does this sound like you?
Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or appropriate discipline;
Minimum of six years of relevant business intelligence experience in large-scale data warehouse/big data projects;
Good knowledge of the theoretical aspects of market practices and their pragmatic implementation;
Experience:
architecting solutions for big data and structured and unstructured data;
in data security, protection and governance in cloud computing;
with ETL, SAS or Oracle BI solutions (an asset);
in Microsoft Azure infrastructure services (VM, VNet, NSG, AKS, AD, Service Endpoint, Private Link) (an asset);
programming in Python, R, Java or other relevant languages (an asset);
and knowledge of Agile methodologies (Scrum, Kanban, SAFe) (an asset).
Knowledge of the damage insurance sector (an asset);
Communication with teams in French and English. Level expected:
French: 4/4
English: 3/4
