Alithya Group is an advocate for workforce diversity and as such, encourages the participation of women in management roles. We belong to the 30% Club, which encourages women’s access to leadership positions.

Love your job!
Are you looking for an exciting new opportunity?
DAVIDsTEA is a leading branded retailer and growing wholesaler of specialty loose leaf tea, offering a selection of signature blends, single-origin teas, and tea-related gifts and accessories through our e-commerce platform and 18 Canadian retail stores. Based in Montreal, we focus on innovative flavours, wellness-driven ingredients, and organic tea. We’re making tea fashionable and fun, and we pride ourselves on offering both the best possible service to our customers and a positive work environment for our employees!
About the Role
We are looking for a
Business Analyst
to join our IT team!
As a Business Analyst, you will be working in collaboration with key business leaders to drive business innovation through understanding and assessing the changing needs of the business. You will be working with a diversified team to help guide the business in identifying key areas of improvement within our Salesforce applications to successfully towards their deliverables.
Sounds like you? Keep reading…
Responsibilities
Identify and suggest system and process improvement opportunities;
Act as the business technologist by solving strategic and operational problems in an integrated way and across multiple technology domains;
Liaison between all areas of business and technology teams to accurately gather, analyze and document requests;
Create, manage, an update existing business process documentation;
Deliver unbiased business application requirements, draft functional and non-functional designs;
Identify project implications at the system and company organization level;
Participate in reviewing and validating process maps;
Oversee & strive for the quality of in-house and outsource development;
Assist in developing, executing and tracking test plans and scenarios;
Assist in the creation of user training and conduct training sessions for the end users;
Define project scope and deliverables that support business goals;
Proactively manage changes in project scope, identify potential crises, and devise contingency plans;
Define project success criteria and disseminate them to involved parties throughout project life cycle;
Plan and schedule project timelines and milestones using appropriate tools;
Identify and manage project dependencies and critical path.
So are YOU our next
Business Analyst
?
Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in computer science, engineering, information systems or a related area of study;
Minimum 3 years of experience as a Business Analyst;
Strong understanding of project lifecycle tools such as JIRA & Confluence;
Knowledge of Salesforce applications, including Commerce Cloud, Marketing Cloud, CDP, Loyalty, Social Studio, and Service Cloud;
Experience in the implementation and enhancement of large scale systems;
Strong analytical skills and the ability to explain concepts in layman’s terms and produce visual representations to support discussions;
Familiarity of software development principles;
Possess an understanding of Lean and Six Sigma methodologies;
Bilingual - Ability to communicate fluently in English is important;
Autonomous, flexible, and proactive;
Detail and result oriented, highly reliable and dynamic;
Team player with great interpersonal skills;
Experience in a retail environment.
Sound good? Then join us in our mission of making the world smile— one cup at a time.
